No significant difference (p = 0.846) was found in mean decrease in Intraocular Pressure between the Selective Laser Trabeculoplasty (

 5.86 mmHg

) and Argon Laser Trabeculoplasty (

 6.04 mmHg

) groups at 1 year or at any other time points, nor were there any significant differences in the rate of early or late complications between the two groups.
